The paper focuses on the design of an interactive visualization tool to reveal biases in AI algorithms, specifically Neural Networks. This involves combining counterfactual examples and abstraction of an NN decision process to empower non-experts to detect bias. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HCI, as the paper deals with human-computer interaction and user-centered design. The second most likely category is cs.AI, as the paper deals with AI algorithms and their biases. The third likely category is cs.CYBER, as the paper deals with the potential social impact of biased AI algorithms. The fourth likely category is cs.SI, as the paper deals with social implications of AI algorithms. The fifth likely category is cs.LG, as the paper deals with machine learning algorithms and their biases.
